ions and variance between the picture and actual product.&l;/li&g;&l;li&g;The Primary material is the main material used to manufacture the product and in addition to the primary material there might also be other type of materials used in the manufacturing of the product&l;/li&g;&l;/ul&g;&l;p&g;.&l;/p&g;&q;},&q;type&q;:&q;HTML&q;},{&q;key&q;:&q;Care&q;,&q;data&q;:{&q;care&q;:&q;&l;p&g;&l;strong&g;Material Care Instruction:&l;/strong&g;&l;/p&g;&l;ul&g;&l;li&g;Avoid or limit direct exposure to sunlight.&l;/li&g;&l;li&g;Dust regularly with a dry soft cloth.&l;/li&g;&l;li&g;Do not leave spills unattended.&l;/li&g;&l;/ul&g;&l;p&g;&a;nbsp;&l;/p&g;&l;p&g;&l;strong&g;Product Care &a;amp; Maintenance:&l;/strong&g;&l;/p&g;&l;ul&g;&l;li&g;Clean your wardrobes regularly to keep them looking new.&l;/li&g;&l;li&g;Use a soft microfibre cloth for cleaning the surface to avoid scratching.&l;/li&g;&l;li&g;Clean the edge and corners of the wardrobe with a cotton swab moistened with water. Keep a dry cloth along with you to dry the area just after applying water.&l;/li&g;&l;li&g;Never use an abrasive sponge as it may result in scratches on the surface.&l;/li&g;&l;li&g;Prevent moisture to remain on your surfaces. Wipe it dry immediately to avoid damage.&l;/li&g;&l;li&g;For sticky dirt, it is better to use a mild household cleaning agent.&l;/li&g;&l;li&g;Do not stand on shelves or place heavy objects as this may cause them to break.&l;/li&g;&l;li&g;Do not close or open the wardrobe doors with force to avoid breaking and damage.&l;/li&g;&l;li&g;Sharp objects can cut right through the surface of the wood, leaving behind unsightly scratches and gouges.&l;/li&g;&l;/ul&g;&l;p&g;&a;nbsp;&l;/p&g;&q;},&q;type&q;:&q;HTML&q;},{&q;key&q;:&q;Merchant Info&q;,&q;data&q;:{&q;merchant_details_image&q;:&q;supplierpng/cb77018518aea054bef1fe9a300a7b8b.png?_v=15&q;},&q;type&q;:&q;Image&q;},{&q;key&q;:&q;Warranty &a; Installation&q;,&q;data&q;:{&q;assembly&q;:&q;Carpenter Assembly&q;},&q;type&q;:&q;TEXT&q;